cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper establishes the equivalence between a class of automata and a fragment of modal mu-calculus logic. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with asynchronous distributed automata. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses a model of computation using finite-state machines. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper deals with graphs and acyclic state diagrams. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possible category as the paper deals with automata and their expressive power.
